# ============================================================
# There is no .env file for this project.
#
# The only secret required to start the platform is the encryption key,
# which is delivered as a Docker secret — NOT an environment variable.
#
# First-time setup:
#   mkdir -p secrets
#   openssl rand -hex 32 > secrets/encryption_key
#   chmod 600 secrets/encryption_key
#   echo "secrets/" >> .gitignore
#
# Then run:
#   docker-compose up
#
# You will be redirected to the Setup Wizard, where you will enter all
# other configuration (database credentials, Discord tokens, API keys,
# etc.) through the browser UI.  Settings are encrypted and saved to
# a Docker volume using the key you just created.
# ============================================================

# Optional: override the app name baked into the Next.js build.
# This is non-sensitive and only needed if you want a custom branding.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_NAME=Baseline Bot
